[{"question":"You never did that, did you?","answer":"I did a couple of the love scenes.","docId":"121118pmt","qSentId":21,"aSentId":22},{"question":"Could you have ever imagined, when you were out there embedded with these troops, that that would happen?","answer":"No.","docId":"121118pmt","qSentId":37,"aSentId":38},{"question":"It is just a total distraction, isn\u0027t it?","answer":"It is.","docId":"121118pmt","qSentId":60,"aSentId":61},{"question":"What do you say to that?","answer":"Well, I don\u0027t think the idea -- the problem is that General Petraeus had an affair.","docId":"121118pmt","qSentId":77,"aSentId":78},{"question":"What do you think?","answer":"First of all, I was substituting for George Stephanopoulos that Sunday as host of \"This Week.\"","docId":"121118pmt","qSentId":91,"aSentId":92},{"question":"Did she act in good faith, do you think?","answer":"I can\u0027t get inside her brain.","docId":"121118pmt","qSentId":108,"aSentId":109},{"question":"That\u0027s a problem, isn\u0027t it?","answer":"Without question, as somebody who was covering the Benghazi story in the months leading up to the election, and also covering the election, it was so politicized with the White House and the administration in a defensive crouch, because they thought every word they said would be twisted and unfairly attacked.","docId":"121118pmt","qSentId":118,"aSentId":119},{"question":"How are you?","answer":"Thanks, Piers.","docId":"121118pmt","qSentId":135,"aSentId":136},{"question":"Do you think it\u0027s healthy for a biographer to be that close to their subject?","answer":"No.","docId":"121118pmt","qSentId":170,"aSentId":171},{"question":"But what would have happened, for example -- with one of your subjects, JFK -- what would have happened to JFK if e-mail and text messaging had existed?","answer":"ELLEY: Yes.","docId":"121118pmt","qSentId":194,"aSentId":195},{"question":"Does it matter if they have affairs?","answer":"I think that\u0027s such a great question.","docId":"121118pmt","qSentId":211,"aSentId":212},{"question":"Like whom?","answer":"Eliot Spitzer would come to mind.","docId":"121118pmt","qSentId":223,"aSentId":224},{"question":"How about Churchill?","answer":"I don\u0027t think Churchill ever had affairs.","docId":"121118pmt","qSentId":260,"aSentId":261},{"question":"Why were you not a fan of General Petraeus?","answer":"Well, the American media has come up with this narrative that he\u0027s the American hero who betrayed by the woman.","docId":"121118pmt","qSentId":313,"aSentId":314},{"question":"Were you surprised when Petraeus got the CIA job?","answer":"I was worried about it because he\u0027s created again -- the military crossing into the CIA is very dangerous.","docId":"121118pmt","qSentId":356,"aSentId":357},{"question":"-- for him to resign?","answer":"In England, it is.","docId":"121118pmt","qSentId":369,"aSentId":370},{"question":"That is quite dangerous, isn\u0027t it?","answer":"Very dangerous.","docId":"121118pmt","qSentId":384,"aSentId":385},{"question":"On balance, are you pleased though that he won the election?","answer":"I\u0027m pleased he won the election.","docId":"121118pmt","qSentId":416,"aSentId":417},{"question":"Why did you want to make this series?","answer":"Boy.","docId":"121118pmt","qSentId":443,"aSentId":444},{"question":"You thought it was really good?","answer":"I think he is tremendous.","docId":"121118pmt","qSentId":514,"aSentId":515},{"question":"You never did that, did you?","answer":"I did a couple of the love scenes.","docId":"121118pmt","qSentId":522,"aSentId":523},{"question":"Of all the Bond girls, and there were so many, especially in the seven movies you made, if I could trap you on a desert island with one of them, and I know it is like choosing your favorite baby, but if I can put you on an island for the rest of your life with one Bond girl, who would it be?","answer":"I\u0027d actually go with my wife.","docId":"121118pmt","qSentId":531,"aSentId":532},{"question":"Really?","answer":"I can say \"I love you\" in Swedish.","docId":"121118pmt","qSentId":542,"aSentId":543},{"question":"I mean, to walk around with people knowing you\u0027re Bond?","answer":"But you get sort of used to it after you have said, \"my name is Bond, James Bond\" 400 times.","docId":"121118pmt","qSentId":549,"aSentId":550},{"question":"Do people make you still say that?","answer":"Oh, yes, always.","docId":"121118pmt","qSentId":551,"aSentId":552},{"question":"Everywhere you go?","answer":"Every interview.","docId":"121118pmt","qSentId":553,"aSentId":554},{"question":"How many women do you think you have seduced because you played James Bond in the last 50 years?","answer":"Been married four times.","docId":"121118pmt","qSentId":555,"aSentId":556},{"question":"So you always just this nice, calm figure?","answer":"I try to be.","docId":"121118pmt","qSentId":567,"aSentId":568},{"question":"Have you been what British people would describe as a bit of a naughty boy over the years, would you say?","answer":"Depends what the definition of naughty is.","docId":"121118pmt","qSentId":571,"aSentId":572},{"question":"What would your definition be?","answer":"I suppose getting drunk, falling over and waking up in strange hotel rooms.","docId":"121118pmt","qSentId":573,"aSentId":574},{"question":"Do you have any regrets in your 85 years?","answer":"I regret I can\u0027t start them all again.","docId":"121118pmt","qSentId":577,"aSentId":578},{"question":"Are you surprised that the Bond franchise is still so successful?","answer":"You didn\u0027t hold that book up high enough.","docId":"121118pmt","qSentId":588,"aSentId":589},{"question":"Are you surprised that it still -- I mean, even more successful than it was 50 years ago?","answer":"No, not really.","docId":"121118pmt","qSentId":594,"aSentId":595},{"question":"You a fan of Barack Obama?","answer":"I\u0027m not going to answer anything political.","docId":"121118pmt","qSentId":607,"aSentId":608},{"question":"Really?","answer":"Because I work with UNICEF and you\u0027re not allowed with the United Nations.","docId":"121118pmt","qSentId":609,"aSentId":610},{"question":"Do you feel that when you travel the world?","answer":"Yes, I think that he, like Reagan, makes an American proud to be an American.","docId":"121118pmt","qSentId":613,"aSentId":614},{"question":"If I could give you five minutes back of your entire life, and it can\u0027t involve marriage or children to relive, the greatest moment of your life, what would you choose?","answer":"I suppose being with my parents when I did something that was worthwhile.","docId":"121118pmt","qSentId":617,"aSentId":618},{"question":"Getting their love and respect?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"121118pmt","qSentId":619,"aSentId":620},{"question":"What would he have made of it?","answer":"He was very happy.","docId":"121118pmt","qSentId":625,"aSentId":626},{"question":"That\u0027s basically been the story of your life ever since, isn\u0027t it, Sir Roger?","answer":"Outnumbered.","docId":"121118pmt","qSentId":632,"aSentId":633}]